bug.short_desc: Window background missing on Opera until mousein/out

long_desc.thetext: Today I tried my app on Opera, and noticed that on any (non-native) window I open the background is missing. See attached screenshot. It appears only after I move the mouse in and out of the window. This is with opera 9.27.
Seem to work fine with Opera 9.60 though.

Created attachment 371 Another screenshot showing tables missing their borders and header...
This is another issue which is most likely related to this bug. This one also works fine on Opera 9.6.
Jonny can you take alook at this Opera issue?

I could not reproduce this issue with Opera 9.27, but instead I found other rendering issues. However, all these issues are gone in Opera 9.61.
Gaëtan, could you try to reproduce this issue in the latest version of Opera?

(In reply to comment #6) > I could not reproduce this issue with Opera 9.27, but instead I found other > rendering issues. However, all these issues are gone in Opera 9.61. > > Gaëtan, could you try to reproduce this issue in the latest version of Opera?
I thought I had already replied to this comment, but seems like I didn't... As said in a previous comment: it works fine (ie I can't reproduce the issue) on Opera 9.60+.
Thanks for this additional information. Unfortunately we will not fix Opera bugs that are related to versions less than the latest official version. It is just not worth the effort.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
